#- §lDocWifi Introduces Bill to give Landowners further rights§0
§0§oBy Nahubi§0
§0
§0On Friday night, DocWifi proposed legislature on the Aquila subreddit that would give landowners more rights under law.§0
§0
§0(cont. next page)
#- The purpose of the Land Rights Act, as stated, is the following:§0
§0
§0§oThe purpose of this bill is to define the rights of land owners within the city of Aquila and in the outlying territory, to designate powers of eviction and demolition, and to grant
#- §opowers of eminent domain to the Government of Aquila.§0
§0
§0Of course, the Act gives the right to land owners protection from trespassing, breaking and entering, and unlawful search and seizure, as well as the right to sell their land.
#- However, the Act would also give the Executive Council the ability to give land out to new residents (rather than the legislature), evict any person found guilty of a crime, and to purchase property from citizens via eminent domain for government use.
#- It also makes it illegal to tax road usage, and officially gives all road blocks from infinite depth and height to the government of Aquila, along with any government building. §0
§0
§0While the majority of these rights are good, it also gives more power to the
#- executive branch of government. It would also reduce the time of citizenship loss after sale of property from "until the next census" to 24 hours after the sale. MrShroom97, who campaigned with the Free Bird Party, promised small government as a principle
#- of his party. However, there is no legal way for the Executive Council to veto an order like this, so his only alternative would be to convince the legislature to vote against the law.§0
§0

